	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=105651><span id= >MoD</span></a><br><span id=notbold>10 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The <b>worn</b> attack cap is 250.&nbsp;&nbsp;This means any items from gear or tribute with +ATK will cap out at 250.  Tribute is considered as a worn effect.<br><br>Currently there is no cap on ATK from spells or songs.  So you can have 250 worn ATK, and haste of salik &amp; scarecrow illusion from chanters, ranger's 2 ATK buff lines, shaman ferine avatar, beastlords Ferocity, and also bard songs.  Plus whatever else will stack with those. <br><br>Additionally, the proc effects from Prismatic and Primal weapons (they proc Avatar) count towards &quot;worn&quot; atk cap. Because it's coming from an item i guess, that's just how they made it work.<br><br>But the buff spell cast from shamans (Avatar &amp; Ferine Avatar) do NOT count towards the worn cap.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Duke Mertine Soulcleanser<br>Lord Protector<br>Drinal Server</td></tr>
